    "actions_taken": [
      "Both injured personnel evacuated to University Hospital in New Orleans",
      "BSEE Houma District office notified orally and written report submitted within 15 days",
      "Onsite investigation conducted on January 3, 2025",
      "Multiple tests conducted with magnetic lifting device and plate",
      "Manufacturer testing conducted on magnetic lifting device"
    ],
    "summary": "On December 25, 2024, a 340 lbs steel plate fell from a defective magnetic heavy lifting device on the Noble Drillship Blackhornet, striking two workers on their left feet. The welder (IP1) and roustabout (IP2) were lowering the plate when it prematurely disengaged from the magnetic lifting device, falling 47 inches. Both workers suffered swelling and contusions and were evacuated to hospital. Investigation revealed the magnetic lifting device had damaged pole shoes creating air gaps that reduced lifting capacity. Contributing factors included inadequate JSA, failure to conduct timeout for safety, employee perceived haste, and inadequate hazard identification.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE Houma District recommends the Office of Incident Investigations issue a safety alert/bulletin regarding this incident"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "magnetic heavy lifting device",
      "plate disengaged",
      "timeout for safety (TOFS) was not called",
      "pole shoes are in rough shape",
      "air gaps between the pole shoe and part being lifted",
      "employee perceived haste",
      "JSA did not have a proper hazard analysis",
      "inadequate stop work authority"
    ]
  },
